Term.Name: Medicines
Term.ScopeNotes: Drugs intended for medical uses

Term.Name: Youth services
Term.ScopeNotes: Includes youth clubs and voluntary youth organisations as well as services provided to young people by statutory bodies

Term.Name: Child protection
Term.ScopeNotes: Safeguarding children from neglect or physical, emotional or sexual abuse

Term.Name: Careers advice
Term.ScopeNotes: Advice on available career paths, the qualifications and other attributes recommended for particular careers

Term.Name: Religious discrimination
Term.ScopeNotes: Discrimination between individuals on religious grounds, in the context of selection for education, employment or promotion.

Term.Name: Public funding
Term.ScopeNotes: Includes any kind of financial support or contract from central, European, regional and local government sources, available to the voluntary sector and community groups, as well as to businesses and individuals; also the funding of public sector projects and initiatives from any source.

Term.Name: Specialist schools
Term.ScopeNotes: These schools receive additional funding to help them raise standards, focussing on one (or two) specialist subject areas while still meeting National Curriculum requirements

Term.Name: Social housing
Term.ScopeNotes: Housing owned and/or managed by a local authority or housing association

Term.Name: Best value
Term.ScopeNotes: The duty of continuous improvement for local authorities as set by the Local Government Act 1999, concerning efficiency, effectiveness and economy of services to the public

Term.Name: Illnesses
Term.ScopeNotes: Diseases, disorders, medical and other conditions adverse to the health of humans. For diseases of animals, use 'Animal health'. For diseases of plants, use 'Plant health'.

Term.Name: Meat and livestock industries
Term.ScopeNotes: Excludes livestock farming and all animal dealings prior to arrival at market

Term.Name: Civil emergencies
Term.ScopeNotes: Includes public emergencies such as widespread forest fires or rail disasters, as well as riots and civil unrest

Term.Name: Violence against the person
Term.ScopeNotes: Excludes domestic violence, sex offences and war crimes

Term.Name: Business management
Term.ScopeNotes: Applicable to public, private and voluntary organisations

Term.Name: Adult and community education
Term.ScopeNotes: Includes all forms of learning and skills development for people over the age of 16, except for formal education leading to a university or college degree

Term.Name: Equal opportunities and diversity
Term.ScopeNotes: Applies to the opportunities that individuals meet in selection for education, employment, promotion, and valuing and using the differences in people to their best advantage.

Term.Name: Older people
Term.ScopeNotes: People aged 55 years or more

Term.Name: Farming
Term.ScopeNotes: Includes arable farming and all types of livestock farming except fish farming

Term.Name: Environmental protection
Term.ScopeNotes: Covers degradation issues and human impact on the environment, as well as conservation and protection measures

Term.Name: Drinks
Term.ScopeNotes: All types of drink except milk

Term.Name: Drug-related crime
Term.ScopeNotes: Includes crime in order to finance drug purchase and crime caused by the effects of drugs, but not offences such as drug dealing, which are against the drug laws themselves

Term.Name: Heritage
Term.ScopeNotes: Historic buildings and archaeological sites, and their presentation, study and management

Term.Name: Animal health
Term.ScopeNotes: Includes animal disease (but note certain diseases are listed separately)

Term.Name: Research and development
Term.ScopeNotes: Use when no one field of research is specified. Where the research is specific to a subject such as physics, use the subject name, in this case 'Physics'.

Term.Name: Health, well-being and care
Term.ScopeNotes: Excludes Defence medical services

Term.Name: Benefits
Term.ScopeNotes: All types of benefit payments except those relating specifically to pensions

Term.Name: Population and migration
Term.ScopeNotes: For internal migration and population distribution, rather than immigration issues

Term.Name: Prime Minister
Term.ScopeNotes: Use for broad profiles of the Prime Minister, or for items about the machinery and activities of the Prime Minister's Office or for more general items relating to the lifestyle and ethics of the Prime Minister. Items that deal with normal duties should be assigned to the appropriate topic-related category

Term.Name: Urban communities
Term.ScopeNotes: Applies to the space, facilities and infrastructure available to communities, as well as social aspects.

Term.Name: Theft and burglary
Term.ScopeNotes: Excludes theft of vehicles

Term.Name: Competitiveness
Term.ScopeNotes: The ability of businesses to compete in local, national or international markets

Term.Name: Manufacturing
Term.ScopeNotes: Includes assembly as well as manufacturing

Term.Name: Ministers
Term.ScopeNotes: Use for items dealing with activities or views of a Minister that fall outside the scope of his or her ministerial responsibilities, or for a broad profile of the Minister. Items that do deal with normal ministerial responsibilities should be assigned to the appropriate topic-related category.

Term.Name: Tax
Term.ScopeNotes: Use this broad category for any tax not specifically listed as a narrower term

Term.Name: Executive agencies
Term.ScopeNotes: All executive agencies, whether they report to Westminster departments or to devolved administrations

Term.Name: Privacy and data protection
Term.ScopeNotes: Measures to protect personal data from unauthorised disclosure or interference, as well as general protection of privacy

Term.Name: Data security
Term.ScopeNotes: Measures to protect data/information from loss, corruption, interference or theft

Term.Name: Drugs use and abuse
Term.ScopeNotes: The use of drugs for non-medical purposes including drug abuse and addiction

Term.Name: Regeneration
Term.ScopeNotes: Social or economic regeneration of districts, areas or communities

Term.Name: Overseas conflict
Term.ScopeNotes: Includes internal conflicts in other countries as well as wars, in which the UK may or may not be involved

Term.Name: Environmental health
Term.ScopeNotes: Health concerns arising from environmental factors

Term.Name: Racial discrimination
Term.ScopeNotes: Discrimination between individuals on racial grounds, in the context of selection for education, employment and promotion

Term.Name: Sexual discrimination
Term.ScopeNotes: Discrimination between individuals on the basis of gender, in the context of selection for education, employment or promotion.

Term.Name: FAO (Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN)
United Nations
Term.ScopeNotes: Includes UN agencies as well as the central organisation

Term.Name: Information and communication technologies education at school
Public bodies

Term.Name: Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development
Personal, social and health education at school
Special educational needs and additional support
Term.ScopeNotes: Educational arrangements for those with learning difficulties, and support for other special cases e.g. talented or gifted children, or those disadvantaged by language or gender

Term.Name: Non-residential property
Term.ScopeNotes: Land and/or buildings in the public or private sector, other than residential property or agricultural land.

Term.Name: Commissions for supplies to government bodies
Contracts for supplies to government bodies
Environmentally Sensitive Areas
Term.ScopeNotes: Designated areas of the countryside which are safeguarded because the landscape, wildlife and historic interest are of national importance.

Term.Name: Policy making
Term.ScopeNotes: Includes the processes by which government departments and local authorities formulate, implement and evaluate policies

Term.Name: Public relations
Term.ScopeNotes: Activities undertaken by an organisation to explain its policies and operations to the public, including media briefings, publishing, responding to enquiries, etc.

Term.Name: Workplace training and development
Term.ScopeNotes: Learning and development while in work, including training courses, conferences, mentoring, etc.

Term.Name: Further and higher education management
Term.ScopeNotes: Includes institutional finance and organisation

Term.Name: e-Learning
Term.ScopeNotes: The application of information and communication technology to learning, teaching, training and/or skills development

Term.Name: Out of school activities
Term.ScopeNotes: Activities associated with school, held out of school hours and/or off school premises

Term.Name: School links with home, community and business
Performance management
Term.ScopeNotes: The process and outcomes of reviewing effectiveness and efficiency in organisations and business units, especially in the delivery of public services. For performance appraisal of individuals, see 'Performance appraisal'

Term.Name: Interpretive centres (museums and interactive science centres)
North-South bodies
Term.ScopeNotes: Bodies set up under the Belfast agreement, representing Oireachtas Eireann and the Northern Ireland Assembly, to discuss matters of common interest

Term.Name: Houses in multiple occupation
Term.ScopeNotes: House occupied by persons who do not form a single household

Term.Name: Business and Technology Education Council courses
English for speakers of other languages
TESL (Teaching English as a Second Language)
English as a second language courses
General Certificate of Secondary Education courses
Family learning
Term.ScopeNotes: Family learning encourages parents/carers to learn together with their children

Term.Name: Learning partnerships
Term.ScopeNotes: With participation from local authorities, schools, colleges, careers offices, community and voluntary sectors, their remit is to improve the planning and coherence of local post-16 learning and hence widen participation in learning, increase attainment, raise standards and help meet the skills challenge.

Term.Name: Voluntary aided schools
Term.ScopeNotes: The governing body employ the school's staff, contribute towards capital costs and have primary responsibility for admission arrangements. The school's land and buildings are normally owned by a charitable foundation.

Term.Name: Voluntary controlled schools
Term.ScopeNotes: The LEA employs the school's staff and has primary responsibility for admission arrangements. The school's land and buildings are normally owned by a charitable trust.

Term.Name: Foundation schools
Term.ScopeNotes: The governing body employs the school's staff and has primary responsibility for admission arrangements. The school's land and buildings are owned by the governing body or by a charitable foundation.

Term.Name: Special schools
Term.ScopeNotes: Schools for groups of children with special educational needs

Term.Name: Supplementary schools
Term.ScopeNotes: Saturday schools and other supplementary provision, usually cultural initiatives by parents.

Term.Name: Educational institutions (adult and community education centres)
Inclusive education
Term.ScopeNotes: Education of children with disabilities in the general school system

Term.Name: Consultations on education
Term.ScopeNotes: Consultation with those potentially affected by proposed changes in education provision.

Term.Name: Speech training
Term.ScopeNotes: Elocution, public speaking and other oral communication skills

Term.Name: Agenda 21 implementation
Term.ScopeNotes: Action at a local or national level to implement the Agenda 21 Treaty signed internationally at the 1992 Earth Summit

Term.Name: Household waste collection
Term.ScopeNotes: Excludes the collection of garden waste or items for recycling

Term.Name: Special waste collections
Term.ScopeNotes: Special collections for removing bulky items of household waste. Hazardous waste is not included.

Term.Name: Civic amenity sites
Term.ScopeNotes: Sites designated by local authorities for the public to bring items for disposal or recycling

Term.Name: Landfill sites
Term.ScopeNotes: Licensed facilities where waste is permanently deposited for disposal.

Term.Name: Light pollution
Term.ScopeNotes: Brightening of the night sky caused by artificial light

Term.Name: Insulation
Term.ScopeNotes: Thermal insulation of buildings, houses, parts of houses and heating installations. Electrical insulation is not included.

Term.Name: Railway companies
Term.ScopeNotes: Includes companies operating trains and/or tracks and associated facilities

Term.Name: Disabled toilets
Term.ScopeNotes: Toilet facilities and installations designed for use by disabled people

Term.Name: Hard to let and easy to access properties
Spiritualism

Term.Name: Church of Jesus Christ of the Latter Day Saints
Self-help for people with learning difficulties
Reading machines
Term.ScopeNotes: Scanned text is converted to large print, Braille or synthesised speech

Term.Name: Accessible buildings
Term.ScopeNotes: Buildings which allow easy access for disabled people

Term.Name: Speech therapy
Term.ScopeNotes: Therapy addressing communication problems such as delayed language, stammering, aphasia, voice problems

Term.Name: Drug rehabilitation
Term.ScopeNotes: Treatment for dependency on any type of drug, including alcohol

Term.Name: Day care centres
Term.ScopeNotes: Centres providing support services and facilities for older people and people with disabilities, during the daytime

Term.Name: Sitting with disabled or older people
Maternity grants from the social fund
Soldiers, Sailors and Airforce Families Association
Age discrimination
Term.ScopeNotes: Unfair treatment of people on the basis of their age, especially where it concerns older people.

Term.Name: Disability discrimination
Term.ScopeNotes: Applies to employees or prospective employees who are treated less favourably because of a mental or physical disability.

Term.Name: Neighbourhood watch
Term.ScopeNotes: Any scheme organised by groups of owners or residents to protect their property from theft or other types of crime, especially with the support of police authorities

Term.Name: Incapacity
Term.ScopeNotes: Inability to work, because of an illness or disability

Term.Name: Play by mail games
Term.ScopeNotes: Includes games played by postal or electronic mail

Term.Name: Living history
Term.ScopeNotes: A re-enactment of history aiming to educate, inform or research a particular period of time by bringing it to life. Re-enactments sometimes focus on special events, such as battles, but more usually are based around day-to-day life at a particular place and time.

Term.Name: Riding schools
Term.ScopeNotes: Establishments which keep horses for hire out and/or for riding instruction

Term.Name: Sports information and ticketing
Term.ScopeNotes: Tickets, reservations and information about sporting events

Term.Name: Adventure activities licences
Term.ScopeNotes: Licences for those offering adventure activities in a commercial manner to people under the age of 18 years, in remote or isolated places

Term.Name: TEFL (Teaching English as a foreign language)
Waterway preservation
Term.ScopeNotes: Protection and conservation of waterways for public enjoyment and recreation

Term.Name: Business finance
Term.ScopeNotes: Raising and managing of funds by business organisations

Term.Name: Key workers
Term.ScopeNotes: Persons employed in a frontline role in the public sector, delivering essential public services in an area where there are serious recruitment and retention problems, and who may therefore be eligible for help with affordable housing

Term.Name: Business planning
Term.ScopeNotes: Applies to public as well as private sector bodies

Term.Name: Council opportunities
Term.ScopeNotes: Opportunities for obtaining business from local authorities

Term.Name: Fair trade
Term.ScopeNotes: A basis for ethical trade with partners in developing countries, aiming to encourage sustainable development and improved working conditions

Term.Name: Fire prevention
Term.ScopeNotes: Includes training and education in fire prevention

Term.Name: RIDDOR (reporting of injuries, diseases and dangerous occurrences)
Royal Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals
Home authority advice
Term.ScopeNotes: Advice from the local authority where the relevant decision making base of an enterprise is located. The advice may cover regulation, good practice and remedial action

Term.Name: NACAB (National Association of Citizen's Advice Bureaux)
Licensed premises transfer licences (sale of alcohol)
Licences to kill or take game
Building and construction licences (materials on highways)
Licences for uploading petrol into storage tanks
Compensation
Term.ScopeNotes: Recompense for loss, injury or damage

Term.Name: Best value performance plan
Term.ScopeNotes: An annual report produced by local authorities detailing current performance levels, actions of the councils, and future performance standards expected

Term.Name: Complaints procedure (local government)
Term.ScopeNotes: Excludes grievances of employees, for which 'Staff grievances' should be used.

Term.Name: Emergency alarms (sick, elderly or disabled people)
Journalism
Term.ScopeNotes: Applies to audiovisual and/or printed media

Term.Name: Town parks
Term.ScopeNotes: For recreational use, not for the parking of vehicles. (See Car parks)

Term.Name: Helplines (care services)
Term.ScopeNotes: Telephone support services, some of which provide care advice while others will deliver emergency response.

Term.Name: ESOL (English for speakers of other languages)
Explosives licences
Term.ScopeNotes: Licences for the storage and/or sale of fireworks and other explosive materials

Term.Name: Mental health and learning disabilities trusts
Portable antiquities
Term.ScopeNotes: Portable archaeological objects discovered by members of the public

Term.Name: Attendance management
Term.ScopeNotes: Applies to job attendance and not to attendance by schoolchildren

Term.Name: Transfer of Undertakings (Protection of Employment) Regulations
Capability procedures
Term.ScopeNotes: Procedures to assess and deal with incompetence at work

Term.Name: Debt management
Term.ScopeNotes: Activities involved in managing the debts owed to the business or public sector body

Term.Name: Budget control
Term.ScopeNotes: Monitoring and reporting of budgets against plan

Term.Name: Spending reviews
Term.ScopeNotes: Reviews which set limits for the expenditure of government departments and, through Public Service Agreements, define the key improvements that the public can expect from these resources.

Term.Name: Local Area Agreements
Term.ScopeNotes: Agreements that take account of local and national priorities for the delivery of public service outcomes in particular localities.

Term.Name: PRINCE2
Term.ScopeNotes: A methodology for project management, widely used in the UK public sector

Term.Name: Organisational development
Term.ScopeNotes: Strategy, planning and implementation to ensure that an organisation and its workforce are appropriately positioned to deliver desired outcomes

Term.Name: Relocation
Term.ScopeNotes: Includes relocation of any kind of organisation or part of the organisation and/or its staff

Term.Name: Electronic document and records management systems
EDRM (electronic document and records management) systems
ERDM (electronic records and document management) systems
Change control
Term.ScopeNotes: Mechanisms and procedures governing the updating of IT resources such as standards, specifications, software

Term.Name: Information
Term.ScopeNotes: Use this term to tag resources that are ABOUT information; not for resources that simply ARE information.

Term.Name: Information architecture
Term.ScopeNotes: Structural design of shared information environments, embracing all stages from information creation through to dissemination and use

Term.Name: Adoption rights
Term.ScopeNotes: Special rights concerning pay and leave for employees with an adopted child

Term.Name: Corporate social responsibility
Term.ScopeNotes: Policies that contribute to the sustainable development of society, considering the economic, social and environmental impacts of business activities

Term.Name: Protection of Children Act List checks
Comedy clubs
Term.ScopeNotes: Venues usually used by stand-up comedians to perform

Term.Name: Customer satisfaction
Term.ScopeNotes: Applies to customers of public and academic as well as private sector organisations

Term.Name: Highers
Term.ScopeNotes: Exams/qualifications within the Scottish Credit and Qualifications Framework, normally taken at the end of the fifth year of secondary education

Term.Name: Standard Grades
Term.ScopeNotes: Exams/qualifications within the Scottish Credit and Qualifications Framework, normally taken at the end of the fourth year of secondary education

Term.Name: AVCs (Additional voluntary contributions) for occupational pensions
